# Satisfactory Calc — Project Overview

**Purpose**: Satisfactory game production-planning UI. Users build a tree of machines with flow rates, belts, clocks, and purity, across multiple named factories in a workspace.

## Tech Stack
- **Next.js 16** (App Router, `src/app/`)
- **React 19**, **Tailwind CSS 4**, **TypeScript 5**
- **Vitest 3** — `npm test`
- Game data: static JSON at `src/data/satisfactory.json`, accessed via `src/lib/db.ts`
- State: React `useState` + `useRef` only — no Redux / Zustand / React Query

## Directory Map
| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/app/` | Next.js routes + API routes (`/api/data`, `/api/recipes`, etc.) |
| `src/components/FlowChart.tsx` | Main component — all workspace/factory/tree state lives here |
| `src/components/flow-chart/` | Flow-chart modals, cards, slice layout, drag, constants, types |
| `src/components/ProductionChain.tsx` | Standalone linear-chain calculator (separate from FlowChart) |
| `src/lib/` | All domain logic: tree, flow rates, storage balance, persistence, planner |
| `src/data/` | Game data JSON |

## Flow Layout
- **Horizontal only** (`TreeLevelSlices.tsx`) — columns by `displaySliceIndex`
- Vertical `TreeLevel.tsx` is retained as legacy component code but not used by `FlowChart.tsx` runtime.
- **Responsive mobile mode** (`<1024px`) keeps horizontal slice columns but shifts controls into the hamburger menu, hides storage rail from main canvas, and removes slice input/output chrome for touch-first navigation.
